events.name: Denver Nuggets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 40 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Denver Nuggets 127-103 on Sunday in a matchup between the top two teams in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 40 as Thunder top Nuggets 127-103 in matchup of West leaders

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 24 points, Kevin Durant had 21 points, nine rebounds and eight assists and the Phoenix Suns beat the injury-depleted Dallas Mavericks 125-116 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker and Durant help Suns hold off injury-depleted Mavs 125-116

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 32 points and Desmond Bane added 30 to lead the Memphis Grizzlies past the New Orleans Pelicans 107-104 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant and Bane help Grizzlies hang on to beat Pelicans 107-104

headlines.description: — Lonnie Walker IV and Quentin Grimes scored 25 points apiece and the Philadelphia 76ers earned a 126-122 victory over the Utah Jazz on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Walker scores 25 as the 76ers open 22-point 4th-quarter lead, hold on to beat the Jazz 126-122

headlines.description: — Max Strus had 17 points to lead a balanced scoring attack as the NBA-leading Cleveland Cavaliers defeated the Milwaukee Bucks 112-100 on Sunday night for their 14th consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers rely on scoring balance to beat Bucks 112-100 for 14th consecutive victory

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 25 points on 10-for-15 shooting to lead the Minnesota Timberwolves past the San Antonio Spurs 141-124 on Sunday night for their fifth consecutive victory and highest score this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves top Spurs 141-124 for 5th straight win on 25-point night for Anthony Edwards

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham scored 28 points, Tobias Harris added 20 points on 9-of-13 shooting and the Detroit Pistons defeated the Portland Trail Blazers 119-112 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cade Cunningham's 28 points help Pistons beat Trail Blazers 119-117

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard’s hook shot at the buzzer lifted the Los Angeles Clippers over the Sacramento Kings 111-110 in overtime on Sunday night to tighten their grip on eighth place in the West.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard's hook shot at buzzer in OT gives Clippers 111-110 win over Kings
